<TITLE> AL cannot restore '72 constitution: Mosharraf </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 28 (bdnews24.com)--Senior BNP leader Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain said Awami League can never go back to the constitution of 1972, the first charter of the nation adopted after independence in 1971. "They cannot restore the 1972 constitution because they cannot remove the amendments to the fundamental principles of state policy made by Ziaur Rahman," he told a discussion meeting on Friday. His comment came hours after Awami League general secretary Syed Ashraful said the government will soon place a bill in parliament to restore the original constitution. Ashraful said on Friday morning: "It's parliament through which the country can go back to the 1972 constitution; not by any order of the High Court or Supreme Court." Secularism and socialism were among the four main fundamental principles in the first constitution formulated by independence leaders. But former president Ziaur Rahman dropped "secularism", and replaced "socialism" with "socialism meaning economic and social justice" and added "Bismillahir Rahmanir Rahim" to the constitution following the 1975 coup in which country's founding president Sheikh Mujibur Rahman was kille
